Articles.Content:
So, all of a sudden, my KSP just decided to take a nose dive in functionality. The VAB/SPH doesn't assemble craft properly.

These are the mods I use apart from Kethane, Texture reduction pack, and Kerbal Engineer redux.

Oh, and this might be useful. https://www.dropbox.com/s/9d34klwbglc7o2x/output_log.txt?dl=0

Edited January 19, 2015 by Raiden

What even is that white thing at the very left of the toolbar?

Also you seem to have duplicate B9 parts, probably from a bunch of different versions.

What even is that white thing at the very left of the toolbar?

Also you seem to have duplicate B9 parts, probably from a bunch of different versions.

I believe the white thing is Deadly Re-entry. This has never caused problems before.

As for the duplicate parts, I don't know WHY that would happen. I've not installed anything new.

Looking at the log, the first NullRef error is being thrown by TweakScale.

This causes a cascade error and FAR to start throwing nullrefs every update frame.

Note that the totally white icon on DRE implies it can't find its button texture file, so also double check your install locations to make sure everything is in the right spot.

Hope that helps you narrow it down,

D.
